  "description": "# Developer Advisory Board Election: Members\n\nFollowing the approval of the Developer Advisory Board [Charter](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/OPerating-manual/blob/main/Developer%20Advisory%20Board%20Charter%20v1.1.md#responsibilities), the Collective will elect 7 Members, from 10 candidates.\n\nThis vote will utilize approval voting. Voting is set up such that you can place a vote for any number of nominees. In the case of approval/ranked choice votes, delegates may vote for themselves, so long as they also cast votes for the remaining elected positions.\n\n\nThis election is a Joint House election, as outlined in the [Operating Manual](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/OPerating-manual/blob/main/manual.md). \n\n\nCandidates:\n\n* [0x937...c1B](https://atlas.optimism.io/optimist-f8bd)\n* [blockdev](https://atlas.optimism.io/blockdev)\n* [Denispro2015.base.eth](https://atlas.optimism.io/denispro2015)\n* [devtooligan](https://atlas.optimism.io/devtooligan)\n* [Kalambet Peter](https://atlas.optimism.io/kalambet)\n* [m4rio](https://atlas.optimism.io/m4rio)\n* [\ud80c\udc23 Odysseas.eth \ud80c\udc22](https://atlas.optimism.io/odysseas)\n* [shazow](https://atlas.optimism.io/shazow.eth)\n* [Vectorized](https://atlas.optimism.io/optimizoor)\n* [wbnns](https://atlas.optimism.io/wbnns)\n\n[This proposal is eligible for Special Voting Cycle #39c:](https://gov.optimism.io/t/special-voting-cycle-roundup-39c/10121)",
